This is the plural of {jIH:n:1h,pro}.

Verb prefixes when {maH:n:2h,nolink} is the subject:
▶ {maH:n:2h,nolink}:{pagh:n:1h} = {ma-:v:pref}
▶ {maH:n:2h,nolink}:{SoH:n} = {pI-:v:pref}
▶ {maH:n:2h,nolink}:{tlhIH:n} = {re-:v:pref}
▶ {maH:n:2h,nolink}:{ghaH:n}/{'oH:n} = {wI-:v:pref}
▶ {maH:n:2h,nolink}:{chaH:n}/{bIH:n} = {DI-:v:pref}

Verb prefixes when {maH:n:2h,nolink} is the object:
▶ {SoH:n}:{maH:n:2h,nolink} = {ju-:v:pref}
▶ {tlhIH:n}:{maH:n:2h,nolink} = {che-:v:pref}
▶ {ghaH:n}/{'oH:n}/{chaH:n}/{bIH:n}:{maH:n:2h,nolink} = {nu-:v:pref}

The imperative verb prefix when {maH:n:2h,nolink} is the object is {gho-:v:pref}.

▶ {ghIq jach qa'rol:sen:nolink}
   {maQ 'oH:sen:nolink}
   {HemHa'choch 'ej cho'choH moratlh:sen:nolink}
  "Then the qa'rol raises voice,
   The signal for Morath
   To lose his pride and claim a throne."[3]

▶ {nuH'e' qengbogh mangghomvam:sen:nolink}
